    {
      "id": "33ee3807d679",
      "name": "hermes-sync rolling rebuild",
      "prompt": "Run the hermes-sync rolling update script. This script pulls the latest hermes-sync git repo, builds a new Docker image, pushes it to GHCR, and does a rolling restart of the hermes containers.\n\nIMPORTANT: This script requires Docker CLI and GHCR authentication. It must be run from the host machine (not inside a container) with access to the docker daemon.\n\nThe script is at: ~/hermes-sync/scripts/sync-and-push.sh\n\nSteps:\n1. Run: cd ~/hermes-sync && bash scripts/sync-and-push.sh\n2. If the script exits non-zero, check what failed\n3. On success, the output will confirm the image was pushed and containers restarted\n\nIf docker is not accessible (running inside a container), output \"SKIPPED: docker not available from this context\" and exit 0.",
