    {
      "id": "37ac85c9e62b",
      "name": "nanobot Upstream Sync \u2014 Daily",
      "prompt": "nanobot upstream sync check for ChonSong/nanobot.\n\nCheck if HKUDS/nanobot (upstream) has new commits that ChonSong/nanobot doesn't have. If there are new commits:\n1. Fetch upstream in the local ChonSong/nanobot clone at /opt/data/repos/nanobot\n2. Create a PR on GitHub (ChonSong/nanobot) against main with the new upstream commits\n3. Title the PR: \"sync: upstream nanobot updates (YYYY-MM-DD)\"\n4. In the PR body, list the commit messages (first 10 max) and say \"Auto-generated by Hermes overnight cron\"\n\nUse Python (not bash) for all git/GitHub operations since the container has Python but may lack curl. Use PyGithub (install it if needed: pip install PyGithub). For git, use /usr/bin/git with absolute paths.\n\nIf no new commits, just log \"nanobot upstream: no new commits\" and exit.\n\nWorking directory for git ops: /opt/data/repos/nanobot\nGitHub token: use the environment variable GITHUB_TOKEN or read from /opt/data/.github-token if present.\n\nDeliver result: a brief report of what happened (new commits found: Y/N, PR created: Y/N, PR URL if any).",
