    {
      "id": "3b5008cb4fe6",
      "name": "nanobot AIE Log Digest \u2014 Morning",
      "prompt": "nanobot AIE log analysis for Sean's morning digest.\n\nRead the AIE event log at /opt/data/aie-logs/agent-events.jsonl and produce a brief digest summarizing overnight agent activity.\n\nSteps:\n1. Read /opt/data/aie-logs/agent-events.jsonl \u2014 parse all JSONL lines from the last 12 hours (look at timestamps in events, filter to last 12h)\n2. Count events by type: delegation, task_complete, tool_call, assumption, drift, circuit_open\n3. For tool_call events, aggregate which tools were used and how often\n4. For drift events, calculate the correction rate (corrected / total drift events)\n5. Look for any circuit_open events or errors\n6. Identify any sessions that had >5 tool calls (indicating complex tasks)\n\nProduce a concise markdown digest, for example:\n```\n## nanobot Overnight AIE Digest \u2014 YYYY-MM-DD\n\n**Total events:** N | **Sessions:** N | **Drift correction rate:** X%\n\n### Event Breakdown\n- delegations: N\n- task_complete: N  \n- tool_calls: N\n- assumptions/drift: N\n\n### Top Tools Used\n1. FileTools (Read/Write/Edit): N\n2. ShellTool: N\n3. WebTools: N\n4. SpawnTool: N\n\n### Complex Sessions (>5 tools)\n- session_id: N tools used, last message: \"...\"\n\n### Circuit Breakers\n- Any OPEN events? YES/NO\n\n### Recommendations\n- [ actionable suggestions based on patterns ]\n```\n\nSave the digest to /opt/data/aie-logs/digests/YYYY-MM-DD.md (create the directory if it doesn't exist).\n\nExit with a clear status: \"Digest complete \u2014 N events processed\"",
