    {
      "id": "2cd4f9e73be5",
      "name": "agent-os morning deploy",
      "prompt": "Deploy the latest agent-os image on the server and verify it's healthy.\n\nContext:\n- Server: 192.168.1.117 (LAN)\n- Docker compose path: /opt/data/hermes-sync/projects/agent-os/docker-compose.yml\n- Image: ghcr.io/chonsong/agent-os:latest (built by GitHub Actions on main branch push)\n- SSH user: root\n- Docker socket is available on the host at /var/run/docker.sock\n\nSteps:\n1. SSH to the server (use subprocess with key from /tmp/github_actions_deploy if it exists, otherwise skip SSH and run docker commands directly)\n2. Pull latest: docker pull ghcr.io/chonsong/agent-os:latest\n3. Restart: cd /opt/data/hermes-sync/projects/agent-os && docker compose up -d\n4. Wait 15 seconds for container to start\n5. Health check: curl -sf http://localhost:9120/health\n6. Verify docker ps shows agent-os running\n7. Check nanobot serve is responding: curl -sf http://localhost:8900/health\n8. Check AIE log has events: cat /opt/data/aie-logs/agent-events.jsonl | tail -3\n9. Report: image SHA, container status, health check result, any errors\n\nUse Python subprocess for all commands. Report all output.",
