      "id": "d4994383fe5e",
      "name": "agent-os: Phase 2 \u2014 E2E verification",
      "prompt": "## agent-os Phase 2 \u2014 E2E Integration Verification\n\n**Goal**: Verify dashboard \u2192 nanobot \u2192 MiniMax end-to-end, fix routing gaps.\n\n**IMPORTANT**: All git/gh operations via SSH to host. Pattern:\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"cd /home/sean/.hermes/agent-os && YOUR_COMMAND\"\n```\nThe host's gh CLI is authenticated \u2014 no tokens in prompts.\n\n### Context from Phase 1\nReview Phase 1's output above to see what was created and any issues.\n\n### Steps\n\n**Step 1 \u2014 Check current routing on host**\n\nThe backend is running at localhost:3001, nanobot at localhost:8001. SSH to host and check:\n\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"curl -s localhost:3001/ 2>&1 | head -5\"\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"curl -s localhost:8001/health 2>&1\"\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"curl -s localhost:3001/api/ 2>&1 | head -10\"\n```\n\n**Step 2 \u2014 Check Express backend routes**\n\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"find /home/sean/.hermes/everything-dashboard -name '*.ts' | xargs grep -l 'router\\|route\\|app\\\\.get\\\\|app\\\\.post' 2>/dev/null | head -5\"\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"cat /home/sean/.hermes/everything-dashboard/backend/src/index.ts 2>/dev/null | head -80\"\n```\n\n**Step 3 \u2014 Check for proxy route to nanobot**\n\nLook for http-proxy-middleware or similar. If `/api/agent` route is missing, add it:\n\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"grep -r 'nanobot\\\\|8001\\\\|proxy' /home/sean/.hermes/everything-dashboard/backend/src/ 2>/dev/null\"\n```\n\n**Step 4 \u2014 Fix routing**\n\nIf the proxy route is missing, add it to the Express backend. SSH in and edit:\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"cat > /tmp/add_proxy.ts << 'EOF'\nimport { createProxyMiddleware } from 'http-proxy-middleware';\n// Add before other routes:\napp.use('/api/agent', createProxyMiddleware({\n  target: 'http://localhost:8001',\n  changeOrigin: true,\n  pathRewrite: { '^/api/agent': '' },\n}));\nEOF\ncat /tmp/add_proxy.ts\"\n```\n\nThen merge it into the actual backend index.ts. The exact edit depends on what the file looks like \u2014 add the import and the route.\n\nIf http-proxy-middleware isn't installed:\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"cd /home/sean/.hermes/everything-dashboard/backend && npm install http-proxy-middleware 2>&1 | tail -5\"\n```\n\n**Step 5 \u2014 E2E test**\n\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/agent/chat -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\\\"message\\\": \\\"Reply with just the word PONG\\\"}' 2>&1\"\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"curl -s localhost:8001/health 2>&1\"\n```\n\n**Step 6 \u2014 Check agent-core sidecar**\n\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"ls /home/sean/.hermes/agent-os/apps/dashboard/agent-core/ 2>&1\"\n```\n\nIf it's empty, create a `main.py` that runs nanobot as a subprocess.\n\n**Step 7 \u2014 Commit fixes**\n\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"cd /home/sean/.hermes/agent-os && git add -A && git commit -m 'fix(dashboard): add nanobot proxy route + E2E fixes' && git push origin main\"\n```\n\n**Step 8 \u2014 Verify CI**\n\n```bash\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost \"gh run list --repo ChonSong/agent-os --limit 3\"\n```\n\n### Deliver\n\nReport:\n1. Was the proxy route missing? What was added?\n2. E2E test result \u2014 did the full chain work?\n3. agent-core sidecar state\n4. CI status after push\n5. Any remaining integration gaps\n",
