      "id": "c6a5672793f0",
      "name": "agent-os: Phase 3 \u2014 PostgreSQL",
      "prompt": "## agent-os Phase 3 \u2014 PostgreSQL Schema Migrations\n\n**Goal**: Create SQL migrations from SPEC.md and run them against the local PostgreSQL instance.\n\n**Local PostgreSQL connection**:\n- Host: `127.0.0.1:5432`\n- Database: `agentos`\n- User: `agentos`\n- Password: `${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}` (set via environment variable \u2014 do NOT hardcode)\n- Connection string: `postgresql://agentos:agentos_secure_pg_pass_2026@127.0.0.1:5432/agentos?sslmode=disable`\n\n**IMPORTANT**: The hermes container uses `--network=host` so it shares the host's network namespace. PostgreSQL is on `127.0.0.1:5432` on the host and is reachable from within the hermes container. Ensure postgresql-client is installed (`apt-get install -y postgresql-client`) before running psql commands.\n\n**Steps**:\n1. `ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no sean@localhost 'docker exec hermes sh -c \"apt-get update -qq > /dev/null 2>&1 && apt-get install -y -qq postgresql-client > /dev/null 2>&1\"'` \u2014 ensure client is installed\n2. Read SPEC.md from the agent-os repo at `/opt/data/agent-os/SPEC.md` (on host, cloned to `/opt/data/agent-os/`)\n3. Read existing schema files at `/opt/data/agent-os/migrations/` if any exist\n4. Generate SQL migration files (e.g. `0001_initial_schema.sql`, `0002_...sql`) from SPEC.md \u2014 one file per logical migration, numbered sequentially\n5. Create a `migrations/run.sh` script that applies all migrations in order using `psql` with `ON_ERROR_STOP=1`\n6. Save the migrations to `/opt/data/agent-os/migrations/` on the host (via `ssh sean@localhost`)\n7. Run the migrations: `ssh sean@localhost 'docker exec hermes sh -c \"cd /opt/data/agent-os && psql postgresql://agentos:agentos_secure_pg_pass_2026@127.0.0.1:5432/agentos?sslmode=disable -f migrations/run.sh\"'\"` \n8. Verify: `ssh sean@localhost 'docker exec hermes sh -c \"psql postgresql://agentos:agentos_secure_pg_pass_2026@127.0.0.1:5432/agentos?sslmode=disable -c \\\"\\\\dt\\\"'\"` \u2014 should list tables\n9. Commit the migrations folder to git: `ssh sean@localhost 'cd /opt/data/agent-os && git add migrations/ && git commit -m \\\"Phase 3: SQL migrations\\\" && git push'\"`\n\n**Verification**: After migrations run, query the DB to confirm tables exist:\n```sql\npsql postgresql://agentos:agentos_secure_pg_pass_2026@127.0.0.1:5432/agentos?sslmode=disable -c \"\\dt\"\n```\n\nReport: tables created, row counts, any errors.",
