      "id": "7aa4b9e1ec87",
      "name": "agent-os: Phase 6 \u2014 CI quality gates",
      "prompt": "## agent-os Phase 6 \u2014 CI Quality Gates\n\n**Goal**: Fix the CI pipeline so it actually enforces quality. No more `|| true` hiding failures. Add missing test infrastructure.\n\n**This job requires BOTH `github-pr-workflow` AND `requesting-code-review` skills loaded.** Load them with skill_view before starting.\n\n### Context\n\nThe CI file `.github/workflows/ci.yml` currently has these problems:\n\n1. Every Python/Node/Go step ends in `|| true` \u2014 CI always shows green even when tools fail\n2. Ruff linting only runs on `packages/nanobot` (path-filtered), misses `packages/observability` and `packages/agent-adapter`\n3. No TypeScript test infrastructure \u2014 frontend (`apps/dashboard/frontend`) and backend (`apps/dashboard/backend`) have zero tests\n4. Go packages (`infra/CasaOS/agent`, `infra/CasaOS/webhook-emitter`) have `go build` but no `go test`\n5. The frontend dashboard backend (`apps/dashboard/backend`) makes API calls to Hermes-style endpoints (`/api/status`, `/api/sessions`) that don't exist \u2014 these need to be stubbed or wired\n\n### Steps\n\n**Step 1 \u2014 Load skills**\n```python\nskill_view(name=\"github-pr-workflow\")\nskill_view(name=\"requesting-code-review\")\n```\n\n**Step 2 \u2014 Fetch the current CI file**\nRead `apps/dashboard/backend/src/index.ts` and `.github/workflows/ci.yml` from the repo (via git clone or API).\n\n**Step 3 \u2014 Create a branch**\nUse `github-pr-workflow` skill pattern: `git checkout -b fix/ci-quality-gates`\n\n**Step 4 \u2014 Fix CI in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`**\n\nRemove ALL `|| true` from the Python, Node, and Go jobs. Each job must fail the build if its tool fails:\n\nPython job changes:\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\nruff check packages/ || true\nmypy packages/ || true\npytest packages/ --cov=packages/ --cov-report=xml || true\n\n# AFTER\nruff check packages/\nmypy packages/ --ignore-missing-imports\npytest packages/ --cov=packages/ --cov-report=xml\n```\n\nNode job changes \u2014 also add test runner if missing:\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\nnpx turbo test --filter='./apps/dashboard/...' || true\n\n# AFTER \u2014 ensure turbo.json has a test task, add vitest if needed\nnpx turbo test --filter='./apps/dashboard/...'\n```\n\nGo job changes:\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\n(cd \"$dir\" && go test ./... || true)\n\n# AFTER\n(cd \"$dir\" && go test ./...)\n```\n\n**Step 5 \u2014 Add test infrastructure for TypeScript**\n\nAdd Vitest to the dashboard frontend if no test runner exists:\n- Check `apps/dashboard/frontend/package.json` for a test script\n- If missing: add `vitest` devDependency and `vitest.config.ts`, create one smoke test in `src/__tests__/`\n- Same for backend: check `apps/dashboard/backend/package.json`\n\n**Step 6 \u2014 Add `go test ./...` to Go packages**\n\nIf `infra/CasaOS/agent/go.mod` exists but has no test command, create a minimal test file:\n```go\n// infra/CasaOS/agent/main_test.go\npackage main\n\nimport \"testing\"\n\nfunc TestStub(t *testing.T) {\n    // TODO: real tests\n    t.Skip(\"real tests pending\")\n}\n```\n\n**Step 7 \u2014 Verify ruff covers all Python packages**\n\nEnsure `ruff check packages/` in CI runs against all three packages, not just nanobot. The path-filtered trigger handles this automatically if the changed files include the packages \u2014 but the ruff command should stay as `ruff check packages/` (not scoped to one subdirectory).\n\n**Step 8 \u2014 Commit and open PR**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"fix: enforce actual quality gates in CI \u2014 remove || true guards\"\ngit push -u origin fix/ci-quality-gates\ngh pr create --title \"fix: enforce CI quality gates\" --body \"Removes || true from all CI steps. Adds test infrastructure for TypeScript and Go packages.\"\n```\n\n**Step 9 \u2014 Verify the PR passes CI**\n\nWait for CI to run on the PR branch. If it fails, fetch the failure logs and fix the specific step that failed. Do NOT add `|| true` to silence failures \u2014 fix the underlying issue.\n\n**Step 10 \u2014 Merge once CI is green**\n\nUse `gh pr merge --admin --squash` once all checks pass.\n\n### Verification checklist\n\nAfter merge:\n- [ ] CI no longer has `|| true` on any step\n- [ ] Python lint + type-check + tests all run or are explicitly skipped with `# skip` comment\n- [ ] TypeScript has at least one test file per package\n- [ ] Go packages have at least `go test ./...` running (even if tests are skipped stubs)\n- [ ] PR merge produces a passing CI run\n\n### If CI fails after your fixes\n\nUse `systematic-debugging` skill to root-cause the failure before fixing. Common causes:\n- Missing dev dependency (vitest not installed) \u2192 add to `package.json`\n- TypeScript compilation error \u2192 fix type errors, don't suppress with `|| true`\n- Python import error in test \u2192 add missing dep or mock\n\nReport what failed and what you did to fix it.",
